summary: I think that the new Venom and new Spiderman would be a really interesting fight to see because Eddy doesn’t want to kill...
body: I think that the new Venom and new Spiderman would be a really interesting fight to see because Eddy doesn’t want to kill Spiderman, who he would no doubt view as a good guy, and Spiderman doesn’t want to kill Venom because he doesn’t kill. So its two guys, beating each other up, trying not to kill each other while Venom mutters about the “sticky inconvenient good guy keeps me from snacks.”

tags: tales of ladybug and cat noir
summary:
Bendy Insects with Dark Felines:
Someone at our house might be watching “Miraculous,” but I am not authorized to reveal who that...
body:
Bendy Insects with Dark Felines:


Someone at our house might be watching “Miraculous,” but I am not authorized to reveal who that might be. I gather the show is quite popular…but somehow embarrassing to the in-house viewer.


We are talking about “Miraculous: Tales of Ladybug & Cat Noir” a French anime style show (“Miraculous, les aventures de Ladybug et Chat Noir”) starring an adolescent Parisian girl named Marinette. Her secret identity is the superhero Ladybug. Her schoolgirl crush is Adrien, whose secret identity, unsurprisingly, is her superhero counterpart, Cat Noir…


Or, en francais:

Chat Noir.


“Miraculous” definitely traffics in some friendly superhero story elements, Marinette and Adrien are simultaneously awkward young people who can’t be cool around cute members of the opposite sex….and powerful spandex clad heroes easily able to dominate evil adults.


Marinette seems to have some qualities in common with Peter Parker…..And Adrien bears a startling resemblance to characters who are stereotypically female in the american superhero universe.


Like the cat ladies, he sports a skintight shiny black catsuit, ears, tail and pointy finger tips. And most disturbingly, he wears a large blingy gold bell around his neck.


I’m conjecturing that the French audience has a more elastic understanding of what is allowed in male superhero costumes and thematics.


Gender elasticity in superhero land is certainly a good thing.


But apparently, I need to work on my drawing of bendy people in spandex suits.

summary: So what exactly was Eddie’s end goal? He finds out an alien race is coming to invade and destroy his planet and his first...
body:
So what exactly was Eddie’s end goal? He finds out an alien race is coming to invade and destroy his planet and his first reaction is to expose ??? Drake ??? Like dude you have more pressing matters than taking down an immoral CEO.


Remember the scene just before Eddie returns to his old workplace to hand in evidence and he says something about getting to the rocket after doing this? Well it just shows that all Eddie cared about was exposing Drake and that’s it. After that, Earth could blow up for all he cares.


It worries me how much this man cares about justice but how little he cares for humanity. Now that I think about it, it just shows how much of an anti-hero Eddie really is.

summary: Tbh I hate it when people characterize Peter as dumb or a goody-two-shoes. Like he’s not an idiot or a little child. Naive, yes....
body: Tbh I hate it when people characterize Peter as dumb or a goody-two-shoes. Like he’s not an idiot or a little child. Naive, yes. Pure hearted, absolutely. Compassionate, always. Just because he isn’t hardened by the world and still likes to have fun doesn’t make him less intelligent or act like a child. He still swears and still understands the gravity of difficult situations. He’s just strong enough to still find his light.

summary: So what I love in this fandom right now, is that everyone has agreed that Peter Parker would be adopted by everyone. Tony...
body:
So what I love in this fandom right now, is that everyone has agreed that Peter Parker would be adopted by everyone. Tony obviously has dibs, with Happy not wanting to babysit, Pepper probably is Aunt May’s ally, and Rhodey is just smiling because Tony is now responsible. Then there’s the other Avengers, Steve likes the kid, Natasha acts all aloof but she’s on full Protect Child mode, Wanda and Vision are taking him to rock concerts and book signings, Clint is going on actual experience, and Sam and Bucky are going “ JFC, it’s another Steve who won’t shut up!” And Strange is trying to figure out what curse or protective shield that keeps the kid alive.

Then there’s the Guardians who arranges play dates with him and Groot. Thor is happy to guide the young warrior, and Loki is willing to cut the kid some slack but maybe talk him into committing a harmless crime or two.

Then we got the crossovers, in the Defenders, there’s Matt who decides to teach Spidey how to throw a punch, Foggy and Karen snickering because the Man Without Fear has to deal with the Kid With No Self Preservation Instincts. The rest has all agreed that Peter is definitely smarter than Danny, but they both have no common sense and should never be alone together.

At SHIELD, Coulson and Agent May have a training program and Fitzsimmons have the lab set up. Nick Fury and Maria Hill have both decided that they will be the Not Cool Parents.

And now over by Venom,there’s Human Disaster Let’s Be Losers Together And Jump In a Tank Uncle Eddie and his alien parasite soulmate. Tony does not like them.

So yeah, a lot of would be parents for Peter.
